	Damn!  I should have hidden this better  d:s

	Anyway, if you're wondering why stanley is called stanley, then
	wonder no longer:

	"Stanley knife [British Proper Noun] - a type of very sharp knife
	with a replaceable blade (from "Stanley", a proprietory type of
	hand tool)"

	You use it to cut things up.  Like wood.  Or samples.

	(Yeah, so what else was I supposed to call it?  "Program to cut
	up samples" doesn't have the same ring to it...)

